{"insight":"Borrowed words must keep their wound.","publicTitle":"Stop When the Cure Changes","plainSummary":"A teaching should travel only when it answers the same hurt and can still be tested in daily life.","atAGlance":"A teaching can sound familiar and still ask for a different life. Before we borrow it, we should ask what hurt it answers and what action it requires. If the hurt, trust, or test changes, we have made something new. New medicine deserves its own name and its own trial.","keyPoints":["Shared wisdom must answer the same human trouble, not only use similar words.","The danger is turning worship or practice into modern self-help.","Test whether the practice changes daily conduct in the promised way."],"match":["repair changes"],"tags":["teaching","practice","wisdom","testing"]}
